{
  "stem": "22959.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- we were anxious to reach the Americans zone.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then-- and then UNRRA took care of the rest.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were placed-- from Prague, we were placed in Bad Gastein in these hotels.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we started to work on our papers, in order to have everything in order, in order to be able to leave Bad Gastein for United States.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We personally, we were dreaming to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were counting the borders, how many borders were left to cross.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were very active partisans, felt good about our-- our past.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In other words, the people who were put in the-- in the concentration camps, they, I mean, they had no choice.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's what's happened.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But with us, we knew that we were fighting against the-- the Germans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We knew that we fought for our loved ones.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we felt that we should organize ourselves.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's when we-- my husband organized the group in Bad Gastein, the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I wouldn't say that we are-- that we are better than the ones who were put into concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it happened that from our areas, they did not put us in concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we-- or they finished us up right there on the spot, or we escaped to the forest.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the ones who lived, you know, in, you know, Warsaw, deeper into Poland, they were forced to go to-- to-- to-- to go to concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that was the difference between us and the survivors of the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I brought it up, because in Bad Gastein, we had people from all over-- from all over Poland, people from-- from different European countries.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were all in-- settled in displaced persons camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
